http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/Thiruvananthapuram/Signed-with-compassion/article14015842.ece

In a compassionate gesture, 2,016 persons, including students, came forward to sign consent letters for organ donation at the venues of the arts festival on Friday.The drive was undertaken by 56 students of the National Service Scheme (NSS) unit at the Government Vocational Higher Secondary School in Poovachal in association with the deceased organ transplantation programme of the government, ‘Mrithasanjeevani’.K.S. Sabarinathan, MLA, inaugurated the drive by signing the first consent letter. — Staff Reporter